b'UIC hosts Toys for Tots Drive'
b'\n\t\t\t\tNovember 28, 2018\t\t\t'
b''
b'Donate a Toy'
b'Donate a toy to a child in need today.'
b'The UIC Office of Preparedness and Response is participating in the U.S. Marine Corps Toys for Tots campaign. Through Dec. 5, UIC will be collecting new, unwrapped toys.'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s been an excellent experience,\xe2\x80\x9d said Julie Grey, emergency management specialist at the Office of Preparedness and Response. \xe2\x80\x9cThe process has been extremely positive.\xe2\x80\x9d'
b'Drop-off boxes can be found at the following locations :'
b'East side of campus:'
b'West side of campus:'
b'On Dec. 7, from 10 a.m. to 11:30 a.m., the UIC community will celebrate at a toy sendoff event. A U.S. Marine Corps truck will be stationed in Parking Lot 1A to collect the donated toys and the campus community will have the opportunity to bring any last-minute donations, enjoy a fire pit with s\xe2\x80\x99mores and hot cocoa, and more. The first 100 attendees will receive giveaways.'
b'For more information, contact the Office of Preparedness and Response at ready@uic.edu, or visit ready.uic.edu.'
b'ready@uic.edu'
